annotationA: GM27569p; Translin (Trsn), together with Trax, forms the Trsn/Trax complex, a ribonuclease that facilitates RNA-induced silencing complex (RISC) activation and has been implicated in many different processes, including starvation-induced sleep suppression in flies
annotationB: Argonaute-1, isoform A; Argonaute-1 is an Argonaute/Piwi family protein, which interacts with microRNAs to form miRNA-induced silencing complexes (miRISCs). miRISCs are guided to target and repress mRNAs either by transcript destabilisation, translational inhibition, or both
